Data Management Assistant - UNDP - Islamabad
Islamabad
Qualification and Experience
Bachelors Degree in Information Systems, Information Technology, Statistics or a related subject.
5 years of relevant information and data management and analysis experience with a national or international organization is required.
Experience in the usage of computers and office software packages (MS Word, Excel, etc.) and experience in handling of web based management systems).
The position will be based in the Economic Affairs Division, Government of Pakistan, while working under the overall guidance of the Joint Secretary (UN). The incumbent will be responsible for maintaining and updating the Development Assistance Database for Pakistan (DAD-Pakistan). The DAD Pakistan is an online management information system that helps EAD promote oversight and transparency of the international development assistance to Pakistan. It is an automated information management system which helps EAD improve the efficiency and coordination of donor activities in the country. The system serves as the main database and data collection and reporting system for the donor and NGO community as it ensures effective access to aid data. In the UNDP structure, the position reports to Chief, Strategic Management Unit, UNDP.
Summary of key functions:
Data management and regular update of DAD
Reporting on DAD
Maintenance of DAD
Data management and regular update of DAD
Regularly collect data on donor assistance to Pakistan UN and other multilateral and bi-lateral agencies
Coordinate with focal person of such agencies for DAD update
Regularly update the financial assistance data on DAD
Make sure the data in consistent and valid
